content:
Delete a Summary Formula Column

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Available in: Enhanced Folder Sharing


To create, edit, and delete summary formula columns in private reports:	
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports

To create, edit, and delete summary formula columns in public and private reports:	
Enhanced Folder Sharing

Report Builder OR Report Builder (Lightning Experience)

Delete a Summary Formula Column in Lightning Experience:
Edit or create a report.
From the Formula Columns section, find the summary formula column you want to remove and click X.
Alternatively, from the Fields pane, under Summary Formulas, find the formula column you want to delete and click Delete.

Delete a Summary Formula Column in Salesforce Classic:
Edit or create a report.
From the Fields pane, in the Formulas folder, find the summary formula column you want to delete and click Delete.

Click Save.
title: Deleting a Summary Formula Column
